{
  "title": "Business Plan Notes",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "fd453a32c5dad846",
      "text": "# Q: Why are you setting up a co-operative?\nOur whole motivation is to empower and grow the commons sector. We are convinced at a deep level that only more effective collaboration and commons-based initiatives have the capacity to renovate human culture so that it can address the challenges that face it in transition to sustainability and fairness.\n# Q: What is your Mission statement?\nWe build tools to empower the global commons.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "d84bd0b2f90eaf4d",
      "text": "# Q: Who is your co-operative for?\nFor commons initiatives of all kinds, worldwide - co-operatives, non-corporates, NGOs, freelancers, open-source teams...\nImmediately, for co-operatives and creatives of all kinds using digital workflows.\n# Q: Define stakeholders and identify the 'key' ones\n- **KEY** Core workers: the team who will design, build, maintain and manage the platform tools and administer the systems.\n - Why: they want to commit to realising the values of the mission in a creative and radical way.\n  - How: co-op will exemplify excellent collaborative and co-learning experience, with a commitment to leading-edge creative work.\n- **KEY** Individual members: freelancer members of the co-operative - using the services and more or less engaged with decision making and direction.\n - Why: The service offers straightforward value propositions - access to high quality tools, less need for cash in achieving goals, increased solidarity, access to trusted collaborators and collaboration tools.\n - How: Good governance, transparent accounting and democratic involvement will encourage deep engagement.\n- **KEY** Member Co-operatives: co-operative businesses and organisations that are members of the platform - from those strongly engaged in the development of the platform, to those who are largely consumers of services.\n - Why: Co-operatives will find significant cost-savings and get easy access to high quality tools and services. Access to a trusted community of skilled freelancers within a mutual credit economy will leverage scarce capital. Collaborations will be easily implemented and administered. \n -  How: Strong collaborative culture will include joint projects with member co-ops, ensuring services closely meet needs.\n- Fellow travellers: Groups or individuals who share the mission statement vision, but for one reason or another are happy to be contributors without becoming members (eg Open-source developers, Trades Unions, teams involved in complementary software projects)\n- 'customers': users of the services who are either ineligible or uninterested in membership.\n- Funders/supporters: individuals or groups wishing to see the mission aims realised.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "d6b4275141f0e0b0",
      "text": "# Q: What is your Commercial Activity?\n\n**OUTPUTS**\n- providing digital tools, services, assets\n- intra-member trading platform (mutual credit)\n- training, education,\n- events\n\n**INPUTS**\n- costs of providing services (subscriptions, hosting, platforms, administration, storage, operations)\n- labour of core team\n- resources for core team (both physical - workspace, tools, equipment; and intangible - training, HR ...)\n- business overheads generally - accountancy, insurance, utilities ..\n- R&D for new services\n- marketing\n- travel\n\n**PROCESSES**\n- Core team will design, build, provision and maintain digital services and member platforms.\n- Value creation will be through making valuable productivity and administrative toolsets available to members through high quality interfaces and modes, with good service backup.\n- innovative services that save time and money and provide new capabilities will be added through development work.\n- development over time of the intra-member trading platform will generate long-term value for all.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "99208eb4a2a0a16f",
      "text": "# CUSTOMER PERSONAS AND THEIR INTERACTIONS\n**FREELANCER - MEMBER**\n**TECH CO-OP - MEMBER**\n**NON-TECH CO-OP - MEMBER**\n**FILM PROJECT - NON-MEMBER**\n**STARTUP - NON-MEMBER**\n**COMMUNITY ASSOCIATION**\n"
    },
